'''Chhiâng-môi-su''' (Penicillin) he fûn-chṳ́ chûng hàm-yû chhiâng-môi-vàn, nèn pho-fái [[se-khiûn]] ke [[se-pâu-piak]] pin chhai se-khiûn [[se-pâu]] ke fàn-chhṳ̍t khì-kiên hí sat-khiûn chok-yung ke yit-lui [[khong-sâng-su]]. Chhiâng-môi-su he kîn-sòng sṳ́-yung ke khong-khiûn yo̍k-phín. 1928-ngièn [[Yîn-koet]] [[Lùn-tûn Thai-ho̍k]] [[Sṳn Mâ-li-â Yî-ho̍k-yen]] [[Se-khiûn-ho̍k]] [[kau-su]] [[Sir Alexander Fleming]] chhai [[sṳ̍t-ngiam-sṳt]] chûng fat-hien chhiâng-môi-su khí-yû sat-khiûn chok-yung. 1938-ngièn yù [[Massachusetts Lî-kûng Ho̍k-yen]] ke [[Ernst Boris Chain]] (1906 -1979),  Howard Florey (1898-1968) khi̍p Norman Heatley (1911-2004) liâng-thô ke thòn-chhui thì-lien chhut-lòi.
